<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Scattered Body Parts Found in Mich. </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	SCIO TOWNSHIP, Mich. (AP) -- Body parts were discovered several  
miles apart off Interstate 94 and are believed to belong to the 
same woman, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
	The first discovery -- a pair of severed human feet -- was made by  
a McDonald's employee Thursday morning inside a restaurant garbage 
bin in this town about 30 miles west of Detroit, said Washtenaw 
County Sheriff's Lt. Brenda Sutton. 
</P>
<P>
	More body parts were found four hours later at a rest stop a  
mile east of the restaurant, authorities said. Then, Thursday 
evening, the head of a woman was found at a landfill in Northfield 
Township, about eight miles northeast of the restaurant. 
</P>
<P>
	Ms. Sutton said the body parts appear to be from a white woman,  
but she declined to specify details, including the possible age of 
the victim. She said investigators know of no missing person who 
matches the description of the victim. 
</P>
<P>
	Detectives say they believe the remains are those of someone  
killed not more than two days earlier, and say the parts are of the 
same body. 
</P>
<P>
	``It's like a jigsaw puzzle right now, and we're looking for the  
rest of the pieces,'' Ms. Sutton said. ``Clearly, the intent was 
for us not to find the body.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Authorities planned to check other landfills today, Ms. Sutton  
said. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
