<HEADLINE> A's Mathews Goes on Disabled List </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	OAKLAND, Calif. (AP) -- The Oakland Athletics placed pitcher T.J.  
Mathews on the 15-day disabled list Friday with right shoulder 
inflammation. 
</P>
<P>
	To take Mathews' spot in the roster, the A's recalled outfielder  
Jason McDonald from Vancouver of the Pacific Coast League. 
</P>
<P>
	Mathews is 1-3 with a 6.50 ERA over his last 18 outings. He  
began the season with a 5-0 mark and an ERA of 1.08 in his first 14 
appearances. 
</P>
<P>
	``We hope to get him back to throwing the way he was in the  
first few weeks of the season,'' A's manager Art Howe said. 
</P>
<P>
	McDonald was on the A's opening-day roster, but was optioned to  
Vancouver on May 22 with a .210 batting average. He hit .326 in 32 
games for Vancouver. 
</P>
<P>
	``We're a little thin in the outfield and we haven't had anybody  
pinch running,'' Howe said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
