<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-02 10:40:13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Davenport Pulls Out of Doubles </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WIMBLEDON, England (AP) -- Lindsay Davenport pulled out of the  
mixed doubles at Wimbledon on Friday to concentrate on her 
semifinal against qualifier Alexandra Stevenson. 
</P>
<P>
	Seeded No. 3 in the singles, Davenport has her first shot at  
Wimbledon's final. She was partnered with Australian doubles ace 
Todd Woodbridge in the mixed event and they were seeded second. 
</P>
<P>
	Davenport and Woodbridge were due to play ninth seeds John  
McEnroe and Steffi Graf in the third round, but with the Wimbledon 
schedule in disarray because of numerous rain delays, Davenport 
decided to pull out of mixed doubles. 
</P>
<P>
	Davenport remained in the women's doubles with fellow American  
Corina Morariu. They advanced to the semifinals Friday by beating 
Nicole Arendt and Manon Bollegraf 6-4, 7-6 (7-1). 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
