<HEADLINE> Millions Set To Jam Highways </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- The nation's highways are about to be jammed  
with millions of Americans looking for fun and fireworks during the 
4th of July weekend. 
</P>
<P>
	AAA estimates more than 37 million people will travel 100 miles  
or more from home over the holiday weekend. That would be the most 
for a July 4th since 1986 when 38 million people hit the road. 
</P>
<P>
	AAA says most people, nearly 32.5 million, will be in cars,  
trucks or RVs. 
</P>
<P>
	Motorists will find prices at the pump a little higher. The  
average price of self-serve regular unleaded gasoline is about 
$1.14 a gallon, up about three and a half cents from 1998. 
</P>
<P>
	Police agencies throughout the country are urging drivers to be  
alert, observe the speed limit, buckle up and keep their cool. 
  	   	
</P>
