<CATEGORY> entertainment </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Harmonica Whiz Popper Hospitalized </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Blues Traveler has canceled weekend concerts in  
Colorado after singer and harmonica wizard John Popper was 
hospitalized with chest pains. 
</P>
<P>
	The burly 32-year-old was taken to an undisclosed hospital on  
the West Coast to undergo tests for chest pains he's experienced 
for a few months, according to a statement from the group's label, 
A&AMP;M Records. 
</P>
<P>
	``Doctors have ordered him to remain as an inpatient to monitor  
his condition, at which point possible preventative steps may be 
taken to improve his current physical condition,'' the company said 
Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
	Blues Traveler, known for ``Runaround'' and ``Buy Anyway,'' was  
to appear at the Red Rocks Amphitheater outside Denver today and 
Sunday. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
