<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> RealNetworks Plans WebTV Upgrades </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	REDMOND, Wash. (AP) -- RealNetworks Inc. will provide  
technologies to upgrade WebTV Networks Inc. products to support the 
latest RealNetworks RealAudio G2 audio format for the Internet, the 
two companies say. 
</P>
<P>
	RealNetworks also will develop a new RealPlayer G2 for the  
Microsoft Windows CE operating system, the companies said Thursday. 
This will enable WebTV to expand listening choices available to its 
users, Dow Jones News Service reported. 
</P>
<P>
	Seattle-based RealNetworks provides streaming-media technology,  
which Internet users employ to listen to music as they download it 
from the Web. 
</P>
<P>
	WebTV, owned by Microsoft Corp., is an Internet TV service.  
</P>
<P>
	Shares of RealNetworks closed Thursday at $77.87 1/2, up $9 or 13  
percent, on the Nasdaq Stock market. 


  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
