</P>
<P>
	Day Runner, down 2 5/16 at 10 5/16  
</P>
<P>
	The Irvine, Calif.-based maker of paper organizers expects to  
lose money in the fourth quarter, compared to a nearly $5 million 
profit a year ago. The company said inventory tightening lowered 
sales to big U.S. accounts, increased product returns and affected 
its product mix. 

</P>
<P>
	Happy Kids, down 1/4 at 9  
</P>
<P>
