<CATEGORY> entertainment </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Boy George Celebrates Pub Reopening </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LONDON (AP) -- Boy George joined a crowd celebrating the  
reopening of the gay pub where a nail-bomb blast killed three 
people in April. 
</P>
<P>
	Several hundred people gathered outside the Admiral Duncan pub  
in central London as it opened its doors Friday, nine weeks after 
the explosion that also injured 70 people. 
</P>
<P>
	``Today is about remembrance, but it's also about moving on,''  
said George, dressed in a black suit and leopard skin top hat. 
``The reopening of the Admiral Duncan pub after just nine weeks 
sends a powerful message to the small but dangerous minority who 
want to terrorize the lesbian and gay and ethnic minority 
communities.'' 
</P>
<P>
	A 22-year-old man has been charged with planting the bomb and  
with two earlier blasts in the London area. 
</P>
<P>
	``This is going to be a celebration and we are going to have a  
party,'' said pub manager Mark Taylor. ``We have got to move 
forward. There is no going back.'' 
  	   	
</P>
