<HEADLINE> Peeping Tom Teen Charged </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	PONTIAC, Mich. (AP) -- A teen-ager accused of using a hidden  
video camera to tape girls undressing has been arraigned on felony 
eavesdropping charges. 
</P>
<P>
	Robert Charles Mickam, 18, of Farmington Hills, was charged  
Thursday with three counts of eavesdropping and installing a 
device. 
</P>
<P>
	Investigators said Mickam secretly videotaped three high school  
girls undressing in his home for hot tub parties and showed the 
tapes to male acquaintances, who in turn called police. 
</P>
<P>
	Detectives have not found the tapes, said Farmington Hills  
Police Chief William Dwyer. 
</P>
<P>
	Without such evidence, the charges should be dismissed, said  
defense attorney Eric Nemeth. 
</P>
<P>
	``From what we've seen, there is no physical evidence tying  
anyone to anything -- just rumors by some teen-agers,'' Nemeth said. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
