<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> 3 Advance to Delvin Miller Memorial </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	EAST RUTHERFORD, N.J. (AP) -- Rum Boogie, longshot Bit O Candy  
and Oolong each won $20,000 eliminations Friday night at the 
Meadowlands to advance to the $400,000 Delvin Miller Memorial Final 
on July 9. 
</P>
<P>
	Rum Boogie, last year's 2-year-old trotting filly of the year,  
turned in the fastest of the three miles in the sixth race, with a 
1:55.2 lifetime best, trotting by Lovelytobehold for a 
three-quarter length victory. Dream Valley OM finished third. 
</P>
<P>
	``When I qualified her, she wasn't that great,'' driver Mike  
Lachance said of Rum Boogie. ``Last week, I was really careful with 
her, and she didn't finish her mile as strong as she should. She 
was strong tonight. She's on her way back. She was better tonight, 
still not herself but much better.'' 
</P>
<P>
	In the first division, the third race, George Brennan guided Bit  
O Candy to a head victory over Justgotafeeling in 1:56.3. It was a 
half-length back to Poster Princess in third. 
</P>
<P>
	``She was good tonight,'' said driver George Brennan, of Bit O  
Candy's first win. ``I expected her to be good last week, but she 
tied up and ran in the turn on me. I thought there would be a lot 
more speed in the race but as it was, I followed good cover. 
Gurfein's crew did a great job getting her right from last week. 
All we have to hope for now is the post.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Oolong, the New Jersey Sire Stakes Final winner, edged Canland  
Hall by a head in the fifth race division, trotting the mile in 
1:56.3. Bloodstock's Chat finished a head back in third. 
</P>
<P>
	``She was real sharp tonight,'' said Oolong's trainer and part  
owner Per Henriksen. ``She warmed up super. We scratched her last 
week because she had a little temperature. We probably could have 
raced her but we have a lot in stakes coming up. We didn't want to 
take any chances.'' 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
