<HEADLINE> Grace Sent to Scranton; Perez to DL </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	PHILADELPHIA (AP) -- The Philadelphia Phillies placed left-hander  
Yorkis Perez on the 15-day disabled list Friday, and optioned 
right-hander Mike Grace to Triple-A Scranton. 
</P>
<P>
	Right-handers Joe Grahe and Steve Schrenk were called up from  
Scranton. Also, shortstop Desi Relaford was transferred from the 
15- to the 60-day disabled list recovering from surgery on his 
right wrist. 
</P>
<P>
	Perez, who has an inflamed left elbow, was one of the club's  
most effective pitchers out of the bullpen this season, compiling a 
3-1 record and 3.94 ERA. Since May 1, he posted a 2.63 ERA, 
allowing 19 hits in 24 innings. His last appearance came Thursday 
when he injured his elbow after pitching 1-3 of an inning, allowing 
a hit and a run, in the Phillies' 12-7 loss at Pittsburgh. 
</P>
<P>
	Perez, 31, was scheduled to undergo an MRI on the elbow Friday  
night. 
</P>
<P>
	``Yorkis has a sprained ligament in his left elbow,'' Phillies  
team physician Dr. Phillip Marone said. ``Whatever the result, he 
will be disabled for at least 15 days. This type of thing comes 
from repetitive pitching, not from just one pitch.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Grace posted a 1-1 mark in 21 games, but was tagged with 46 hits  
and 25 earned runs in 30 innings for a 7.50 ERA. 
</P>
<P>
	Schrenk, 30, was 3-1 in 32 relief appearances for Scranton with  
a 2.93 ERA and two saves. It will be his first stint in the major 
leagues. 
</P>
<P>
	Grahe, 31, had a team-high 10 saves in 19 games with the Red  
Barons and had a 0-1 record with a 4.24 ERA. He has spent parts of 
six seasons in the majors, most recently with Colorado in 1995, 
when he was 4-3 in 17 games. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
