<HEADLINE> Lineup for Sunday's TV News Shows  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	Lineup for the Sunday TV news shows:  

</P>
<P>
	ABC's ``This Week'' -- Topics: Hillary Rodham Clinton and the  
N.Y. Senate campaign, tax cuts and Medicare. Guests: Former Reps. 
Susan Molinari, R-N.Y., and Geraldine Ferraro, D-N.Y., Senate 
Minority Leader Tom Daschle, D-S.D., and Rep. John Kasich, R-Ohio. 

</P>
<P>
                              *------	 

</P>
<P>
	CBS' ``Face the Nation'' -- Topics: Hillary Rodham Clinton and  
the N.Y. Senate race, politics and campaign finance reform. Guests: 
Sens. Robert Torricelli, D-N.J., Mitch McConnell, R-Ky., and John 
McCain, R-Ariz. 

</P>
<P>
                              *------	 

</P>
<P>
	NBC's ``Meet the Press'' -- Topics: Clinton's Medicare proposal,  
GOP agenda, Hillary Rodham Clinton and the N.Y. Senate race, and 
presidential politics. Guests: Health and Human Services Secretary 
Donna Shalala, House Speaker Dennis Hastert, R-Ill., and Reps. 
Charles Rangel, D-N.Y., and Rick Lazio, R-N.Y. 

</P>
<P>
                              *------	 

</P>
<P>
	CNN's ``Late Edition'' -- Topics: Medicare, presidential politics  
and Hillary Rodham Clinton's N.Y. Senate race. Guests: Sens. Orrin 
Hatch, R-Utah, and Dick Durbin, D-Ill.; former Rep. Susan Molinari, 
R-N.Y.; Lisa Caputo, former press secretary to Mrs. Clinton, and 
White House Budget Director Jack Lew. 

</P>
<P>
                              *------	 

</P>
<P>
	``Fox News Sunday'' -- Topics: Presidential politics, Hillary  
Rodham Clinton and the N.Y. Senate race, and Hollywood's role in 
social problems. Guests: Republican presidential candidate Steve 
Forbes; former Sen. Alfonse D'Amato, R-N.Y.; Rep. Nita Lowey, 
D-N.Y., film critic Michael Medved and David Horowitz of the Center 
for the Study of Popular Culture. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
