<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Tobacco Giant RJR Has New President </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WINSTON-SALEM (AP) -- Andrew J. Schindler was elected chairman,  
president and CEO of R.J. Reynolds Tobacco Holdings Inc. on Friday 
after leading the company's tobacco subsidiary since 1995. 
</P>
<P>
	The holding company board of directors chose Schindler, who  
joined the RJR organization in 1974 and most recently was president 
and CEO of Reynolds Tobacco Co., a wholly owned subsidiary. 
</P>
<P>
	Schindler, a native of Harrisburg, Pa., holds a bachelor's  
degree from Franklin and Marshall College, and a master of business 
administration from The Wharton School of the University of 
Pennsylvania. He also served in the Army, reaching the rank of 
captain. 
</P>
<P>
	R.J. Reynolds Tobacco is the nation's second-largest tobacco  
company and the maker of Winston, Camel, Salem and Doral brands. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
