<HEADLINE> Euro Rises Against the Dollar </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- The euro crawled back against the dollar Friday,  
a day after dropping to another low against the U.S. currency. 
</P>
<P>
	In late New York trading, the euro was quoted at $1.0240, up  
from $1.0229 late Thursday. The dollar also was quoted at 121.01 
Japanese yen, up from 120.78. 
</P>
<P>
	The euro had tumbled on Thursday after the European Central Bank  
chose not to follow the U.S. Federal Reserve in lowering interest 
rates. Perceptions of slower growth in Europe versus the United 
States have been wearing down on the euro currency. 
</P>
<P>
	The dollar also was quoted at 1.5687 Swiss francs, slightly down  
from 1.5692, and 1.4645 Canadian dollars, off from 1.4729. The 
British pound edged up to $1.5783 from $1.5728. 
</P>
<P>
	Currencies of the 11 countries participating in the euro are no  
longer traded separately and are tied to the euro by a fixed rate. 
Based on Friday's euro rate, the dollar was worth: 1.9099 German 
marks, down from 1.9120; 6.4061 French francs, down from 6.4144; 
and 1,890.36 Italian lire, down from 1,893.94. 
</P>
</TEXT>
