<HEADLINE> Stocks Inch Higher in Early Trading / Wall Street Report  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- The Dow Jones industrial average is up two  
points in today's early going. Advancers on the New York Stock 
Exchange hold a 10-9 lead over decliners. 
</P>
<P>
	The Nasdaq Composite Index is up seven points and the S&AMP;P 500  
Index is up one point. 
</P>
<P>
	The Nasdaq composite and the S&AMP;P 500 closed yesterday at record  
highs. 
</P>
<P>
	And the Dow Jones industrial average has put together a four-day  
advance during which it's gained more than 513 points. 
</P>
<P>
	With an advance of just four points or more today, the Dow would  
have its biggest weekly point-gain on record. 
</P>
<P>
	Already today, the Labor Department has released its June  
unemployment report. 
</P>
<P>
	And while the report showed job growth, and an increase in  
wages, analysts say it's not likely enough to increase fears of 
inflation. 
</P>
<P>
	The bond market is little changed following the labor report.  
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
