<CATEGORY> entertainment </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> King Said To Be Progressing Well </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LEWISTON, Maine (AP) -- Stephen King has already faced the  
frightening prospect of physical therapy. He's now ready to put 
some weight on his right leg, the one broken in a car accident two 
weeks ago. 
</P>
<P>
	The horror novelist has been moving around in a wheelchair and  
has begun rehabilitation work, officials at Central Maine Medical 
Center said Friday. 
</P>
<P>
	King has also undergone another minor operation, his fifth so  
far, and he is said to be progressing well. 
</P>
<P>
	King was hit by a van while walking along the shoulder of a  
highway near his summer home in North Lovell on June 19. He 
suffered multiple broken bones in his right leg, along with a 
punctured lung, broken ribs and cuts on his head. 
</P>
<P>
	King remains in stable but serious condition. Hospital officials  
said he has no more surgery scheduled. No date has been set for his 
release. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
