<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Wimbledon Glance </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WIMBLEDON, England (AP) -- A brief look at what happened Friday  
on the 11th day of the Wimbledon tennis championships 
</P>
<P>
	Weather -- Warm, sunny and dry. High temperature was 77  
Fahrenheit. 
</P>
<P>
	Attendance -- 32,453, a record for the second Friday. Last year  
on the 11th day, attendance was 28,257, the previous record. The 
total attendance so far is 396,701, an increase of 26,106 over last 
year. 
</P>
<P>
	Seeded quarterfinal winners -- Men: No. 1 Pete Sampras over No. 7  
Mark Philippoussis, No. 2 Pat Rafter over No. 8 Todd Martin, No. 4 
Andre Agassi over No. 11 Gustavo Kuerten, No. 6 Tim Henman over 
Cedric Pioline, 
</P>
<P>
	Quarterfinal winners -- Women: Alexandra Stevenson against Jelena  
Dokic. 
</P>
<P>
	Upsets -- No. 8 Nathalie Tauziat, by Mirjana Lucic.  
</P>
<P>
	Stat of the Day -- Alexandra Stevenson became the first qualifier  
in Wimbledon history to reach the women's semifinals. 
</P>
<P>
	Quote of the Day -- ``Our kissing seems to be working well.'' -  
John McEnroe, after reaching the semifinals of the mixed doubles 
with Steffi Graf. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
