<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Two Fillies Moving Up and Down </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Gather The Day will move up and Sapphire n' Silk  
will move down in the Prioress for 3-year-old fillies, one of two 
stakes Saturday at Belmont Park. 
</P>
<P>
	In the other race, Notoriety and Optic Nerve, 1-2 in the  
7-furlong Jaipur, will meet again in the one-mile Poker on the 
grass. 
</P>
<P>
	Sunday's stakes doubleheader will be the 7-furlong Tom Fool  
Handicap and the 5 1/2-furlong Tremont for 2-year-olds. Carter 
Handicap winner Artax, 117, and Affirmed Success, 119, head a 
six-horse field for the $150,000 Tom Fool. More Than Ready, 119, 
will spot six rivals from four to six pounds in the $100,000 
Tremont. 
</P>
<P>
	Belmont's Fourth of the July weekend will conclude Monday with  
the $400,000 Suburban Handicap in which one of the probables is 
Behrens, winner of the Massachusetts Handicap. 
</P>
<P>
	Gather The Day, unbeaten in four starts, all at 6 furlongs, will  
make her stakes debut in the 6-furlong Prioress 
</P>
<P>
	Sapphire n'Silk will drop down in distance after having finished  
fifth in Belmont's one-mile Acorn after setting the pace. She had 
won her three previous starts, including the La Troienne at 
Churchill Downs. 
</P>
<P>
	Both fillies will get plenty of competition in the $150,000  
Prioress. Also in the 10-horse field are Confessional, the 1998 
Frizette winner; Paved in Gold, second in the Nassau County at 
Belmont, and Things Change, winner of the Adirondack and Spinaway 
last year at Saratoga. 
</P>
<P>
	Another starter will be Show Me The Stage, winner of Calder's  
Azalea Breeders' Cup, high-weighted at 121 pounds with Sapphire 
n'Silk. Paved in Gold, Gather The Day, Confessional and Things 
Change each will carry 118 pounds. 
</P>
<P>
	Notoriety and Optic Nerve each will carry 116 pounds in the  
$100,000-added Poker. High-weighted at 118 pounds in the 11-horse 
field is Rob'n Gin, who has sustained narrow losses in three graded 
stakes this year. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
