<HEADLINE> Philippoussis Sidelined 4-6 Weeks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WIMBLEDON, England (AP) -- Mark Philippoussis will be sidelined  
four to six weeks with torn cartilage in his left knee and will 
miss Australia's Davis Cup quarterfinal against the United States 
in Boston July 16-18. 
</P>
<P>
	Philippoussis was injured when he was a set up against defending  
champion Pete Sampras in Friday's Wimbledon quarterfinal. He 
retired from the match, saying something had ``clicked'' in his 
knee. 
</P>
<P>
	Philippoussis' coach, Gavin Hopper, said an MRI revealed the  
cartilage damage. 
</P>
<P>
	``The rest of the knee is sound,'' Hopper said. ``Mark will  
return to the United States and undergo an arthroscopy and seek 
further medical treatment.'' 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
